It's always fun (to me) to encode these silent films and work out the proper frame rate. You must remember that both the camera and projector were hand cranked in those days. Therefore it's pretty much impossible to nail the frame rate perfectly, but usually you can get it pretty close. I encoded test clips from several sections of the film reducing the rate a little at a time until the dupes went away, then I encoded the entire film. You got to love srestore and the frate variable!

